  "body": "Version\n\nkubernetes v1.3.6\n\nDescription\n\nAll pods using a ceph persistent storage are in state : \nUnable to mount volumes for pod ... : rbd: image ext4-0002 is locked by other nodes\n\nSteps To Reproduce\n\nAll pods were running correctly on all nodes\nA node crash during the week-end (don't know why wet)\nCurrent Result\n\nAll pods using ceph persistent volumes are in this state.\nOn the ceph cluster, each rbd has one exclusive lock\n\nExpected Result\n\nUnlock the rbd before mounting it on another node\n\nThe problem was discussed here https://github.com/openshift/origin/issues/7983 but seems like this is the most appropriate place.\n\nThe problem is the same in v1.3.6 as the code handling this is the same.\n\nI seems relevant to this https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/10563#issuecomment-128361389 and maybe to this https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/20262 \n",
